			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerTitleCompanyLabel">Chief Executive Officer, Vicarious Visions, Inc.</span></td>
		        </tr>
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">Karthik has led Vicarious Visions (an independent video game development company that has grown to become a leader in portable and home console game markets) since its formation in 1994. He's been in the gaming business for thirteen years and has had diverse roles ranging from programming, art / animation to marketing and public relations. He holds degrees in Computer Science and Psychology from Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute. Vicarious Visions was originally founded by brothers Karthik and Guha Bala while they were in high school. It was incorporated in 1994 while Karthik was a student at Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute.  With his brother Guha Bala, who serves as President, they have built a world-class development team and a track record of hit titles based on blockbuster entertainment brands such as Spider-Man, Tony Hawk, Star Wars, Doom, Crash Bandicoot, Spongebob Squarepants, Shrek and many others.</span></td>
